discussion_comments.comment_body:
packed layout can be more efficient, less pointer access usually means less tlb miss

```cpp
offset_blob.create(outw, outh, elemsize * 4, 4, opt.workspace_allocator);
value_blob.create(outw, outh, elemsize * 2, 2, opt.workspace_allocator);
```

or even merge the offset and value blob into one
```cpp
offset_value_blob.create(outw, outh, elemsize * 6, 6, opt.workspace_allocator);
```


The same applies for bicubic and 4d routines

